WEBVTT

00:07.708 --> 00:08.242
‐ Previously on "The Purge"...

00:09.576 --> 00:10.377
‐ There should be more
Benjamins in here.

00:10.410 --> 00:11.545
‐ Not here.
We count later.

00:11.578 --> 00:13.580
‐ I need your expertise
on something.

00:13.614 --> 00:14.314
‐ [groaning]

00:14.348 --> 00:16.583
‐ Armed robbery.

00:16.617 --> 00:18.252
‐ Darren!

00:18.285 --> 00:20.587
Son, I need your help.
Somebody tried to Purge me.

00:20.621 --> 00:22.523
‐ Dad, somebody put a bounty
on your head.

00:22.556 --> 00:23.957
‐ Oh, my God.

00:23.991 --> 00:25.626
‐ Hey, man.
‐ What happened?

00:25.659 --> 00:26.660
‐ We got jumped.

00:26.693 --> 00:28.996
[blade slicing, man screams]

00:29.029 --> 00:30.597
But it turned out okay.

00:30.631 --> 00:32.633
‐ Do you still think
about violence?

00:32.666 --> 00:35.869
‐ All I think about
is violence.

00:35.903 --> 00:37.337
‐ New Orleans
Police Department.

00:37.371 --> 00:39.006
Come out with your hands up!

00:39.039 --> 00:40.607
‐ It's my song, guys.

00:40.641 --> 00:42.309
I'm coming out,
and I'm unarmed!

00:42.342 --> 00:44.311
‐ Hands up!

00:44.344 --> 00:46.580
You hereby forfeit your rights
as a United States citizen.

00:46.613 --> 00:49.950
Anything you say or do,
by action or inaction,

00:49.983 --> 00:53.153
will be held against you
in a court of law.

00:54.321 --> 00:57.324
[chains rattling]

01:02.195 --> 01:04.498
‐ Sorry.
Sorry I'm late.

01:05.532 --> 01:08.135
I was appointed by the court
to your defense

01:08.168 --> 01:09.336
and due process,

01:09.369 --> 01:12.539
under Amendment
29 of the U. S. Constitution.

01:12.573 --> 01:14.374
I looked over your file.

01:14.408 --> 01:15.642
It's pretty cut and dry.

01:15.676 --> 01:17.711
I'm gonna recommend
you plead guilty.

01:19.580 --> 01:21.481
I'm sorry.
I forgot my manners.

01:21.515 --> 01:24.618
How are you doing today?

01:24.651 --> 01:26.386
[tense music]

01:26.420 --> 01:28.088
‐ Never been better.

01:28.121 --> 01:35.162
♪ ♪

01:42.235 --> 01:47.140
‐ All right.
Case 20854.

01:47.174 --> 01:50.711
Citizen Thomas Adrian Ortiz.
Age 38.

01:50.744 --> 01:52.613
Accused of armed robbery
and trespassing

01:52.646 --> 01:54.548
occurring on March the 22nd.

01:54.581 --> 01:56.283
‐ That's correct,
your honor.

01:56.316 --> 01:58.318
As such, we request
the defendant be categorized

01:58.352 --> 02:01.755
and sentenced
as a level R major felon.

02:01.788 --> 02:04.558
‐ And what evidence will you
offer to support the charges?

02:04.591 --> 02:06.426
‐ Exhibits 1 through 34.

02:06.460 --> 02:10.097
Our CCTV footage pulled
from the morning of March 22nd.

02:10.130 --> 02:11.131
All angles,
audio,

02:11.164 --> 02:14.835
and coordinates
have been NFFA verified.

02:14.868 --> 02:17.404
As you can see, the defendant
is clearly on private property

02:17.437 --> 02:20.240
after the last Purge
siren ended,

02:20.273 --> 02:23.377
making his actions criminal.

02:23.410 --> 02:26.213
‐ How do you plead?

02:26.246 --> 02:29.650
Son, are you fixing to flat‐out
lie to this court?

02:29.683 --> 02:32.219
♪ ♪

02:32.252 --> 02:33.887
‐ Plead guilty.
Beg for mercy.

02:33.920 --> 02:37.157
♪ ♪

02:37.190 --> 02:38.558
‐ Guilty Your Honor,
but, uh‐‐

02:38.592 --> 02:40.427
‐ But?

02:40.460 --> 02:42.429
‐ I know this technically
qualifies as a level R,

02:42.462 --> 02:44.564
but all I did was move
a bag of cash from point A

02:44.598 --> 02:45.899
to point B,

02:45.932 --> 02:48.101
and I missed the property line
by a few inches.

02:48.135 --> 02:50.337
That's bad timing.
I'm not a threat.

02:50.370 --> 02:51.872
You have my records there.

02:51.905 --> 02:53.640
I served the community well
for many years.

02:53.674 --> 02:55.709
I don't have
any criminal history.

02:55.742 --> 03:00.347
‐ Well, years of acting right
doesn't give you free reign.

03:00.380 --> 03:02.549
We're not here to review
your whole damn life.

03:02.582 --> 03:04.251
Let the record state that you,

03:04.284 --> 03:06.687
the defendant,
have entered a plea of guilty.

03:06.720 --> 03:10.023
‐ Your Honor‐‐
‐ Case 20854 is now closed.

03:10.057 --> 03:12.859
Like all parties guilty
of a level R crime,

03:12.893 --> 03:14.394
defendant is hereby
sentenced to‐‐

03:14.428 --> 03:16.430
‐ Wait, Your Honor.
Hold on, please.

03:16.463 --> 03:18.832
Please.
‐ To death.

03:18.865 --> 03:22.402
Execution will be carried out
in 356 days,

03:22.436 --> 03:23.870
on next Purge Night.

03:23.904 --> 03:24.871
‐ I don't‐‐
I don't deserve this.

03:24.905 --> 03:26.106
I didn't hurt anyone.

03:26.139 --> 03:29.209
‐ If he so chooses,
he may enter the auction,

03:29.242 --> 03:32.646
and 5% of all payments will be
awarded to the next of kin.

03:32.679 --> 03:33.647
‐ Wait a minute.
‐ Bailiffs.

03:33.680 --> 03:34.981
‐ We're talking about
a level R.

03:35.015 --> 03:36.750
This is‐‐this is ridiculous.
No, wait!

03:36.783 --> 03:38.552
Your Honor.
Your Honor!

03:38.585 --> 03:41.455
‐ Get him out of here!
‐ This is bullshit, Your Honor!

03:41.488 --> 03:44.458
You can't do this to me!
This is not justice!

03:44.491 --> 03:46.693
You better
fucking do something!

03:46.727 --> 03:49.796
[dramatic music]

03:49.830 --> 03:56.837
♪ ♪

04:03.877 --> 04:06.813
[tense music]

04:06.847 --> 04:08.014
♪ ♪

04:08.048 --> 04:09.850
‐ I need a little liquid
courage before tonight.

04:09.883 --> 04:11.651
‐ Yeah, and I need you
on your toes.

04:11.685 --> 04:14.688
You know what
we're gonna find out there.

04:14.721 --> 04:16.323
‐ You really think
it'll be that bad?

04:16.356 --> 04:18.692
‐ Yeah.
I do.

04:18.725 --> 04:21.828
‐ Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to Purge Night.

04:21.862 --> 04:24.598
Our city attracts a lot
of people on Purge Night,

04:24.631 --> 04:26.533
and this year,
some of those people

04:26.566 --> 04:29.669
are calling for open season
on anyone with a badge.

04:29.703 --> 04:32.205
Officers have been given a list
of the recent arrests

04:32.239 --> 04:34.007
and parolees.

04:34.040 --> 04:37.344
Watch out for anyone you gave
so much as a parking ticket to.

04:37.377 --> 04:38.678
Everybody changes here.

04:38.712 --> 04:40.714
No uniforms
on the street tonight.

04:40.747 --> 04:42.516
I want to see each
and every one of you back here

04:42.549 --> 04:44.684
first thing tomorrow.

04:44.718 --> 04:47.954
We strongly advise
that you stay home tonight.

04:47.988 --> 04:51.892
♪ ♪

04:51.925 --> 04:53.326
‐ Let's roll.

04:53.360 --> 04:54.995
‐ We really doing this?

04:55.028 --> 04:57.864
‐ You want to try
to arrest Caruso again?

04:57.898 --> 05:00.367
Have the case kicked again?

05:00.400 --> 05:03.503
Caruso's responsible for half
of the drug crime in the city.

05:03.537 --> 05:05.772
So let's use the Purge
to end this piece of shit

05:05.806 --> 05:07.240
and do something good.

05:07.274 --> 05:08.742
‐ Hear, hear.

05:08.775 --> 05:10.477
‐ I understand what you're
trying to do,

05:10.510 --> 05:14.848
but officially, this is
not department sanctioned.

05:14.881 --> 05:18.652
I recommend walking away.
Now.

05:18.685 --> 05:20.387
‐ Anybody who wants
to leave can.

05:20.420 --> 05:21.388
No hard feelings.

05:21.421 --> 05:28.428
♪ ♪

05:32.599 --> 05:34.601
‐ Okay.

05:34.634 --> 05:37.003
Thank you.

05:37.037 --> 05:39.306
Be careful out there tonight.

05:39.339 --> 05:43.310
♪ ♪

05:43.343 --> 05:44.477
‐ Tommy, what's the timeline?

05:44.511 --> 05:47.647
‐ District four reports
a possible criminal activity.

05:47.681 --> 05:50.417
I need my best eyes on them.
[beeps]

05:50.450 --> 05:53.019
This guy was spotted
multiple times

05:53.053 --> 05:56.423
driving within 1,000 feet
of the tarmac in Overton.

05:56.456 --> 05:58.758
Cameras never caught
a clear view of his face.

05:58.792 --> 06:02.696
‐ Is that a crime?
‐ No, but it's suspicious.

06:02.729 --> 06:05.432
Protocol says we need
an ID on the driver.

06:05.465 --> 06:07.434
‐ Get his face,
and then get his record.

06:07.467 --> 06:10.303
Let me know if there's anything
I need to kick upstairs.

06:10.337 --> 06:12.806
‐ You will have it
by the end of the day.

06:12.839 --> 06:15.242
‐ So who is this mystery man?

06:15.275 --> 06:17.344
‐ Um...

06:17.377 --> 06:18.979
♪ ♪

06:19.012 --> 06:22.182
Just give me a sec.

06:22.215 --> 06:24.618
[cell phone trilling]

06:24.651 --> 06:25.619
‐ What up?
You've reached Darren.

06:25.652 --> 06:26.987
You know what to do
at the tone.

06:27.020 --> 06:28.855
[cell phone beeps]

06:28.889 --> 06:32.359
‐ Uh, Mr. Moore, this is Esme
Carmona calling again.

06:32.392 --> 06:33.693
Call me back.

06:33.727 --> 06:35.462
I have something
you need to see.

06:35.495 --> 06:38.331
♪ ♪

06:38.365 --> 06:40.133
‐ Thanks for agreeing to meet
so last minute.

06:40.166 --> 06:42.369
How you doing?

06:42.402 --> 06:44.337
‐ I could use
a good night's sleep.

06:44.371 --> 06:46.139
‐ I'm working on that.

06:46.172 --> 06:47.974
Your neighbor's bank records
checked out.

06:48.008 --> 06:50.810
Nothing connecting
the Cartwrights to Purge Night.

06:50.844 --> 06:52.712
‐ So Steve, he's an asshole,
but not a murderer.

06:52.746 --> 06:54.381
All right.

06:54.414 --> 06:57.083
Well, that was a long shot.

06:57.117 --> 06:58.418
We barely know them.

06:58.451 --> 06:59.753
‐ That doesn't mean
he doesn't know you,

06:59.786 --> 07:01.254
and I check out everyone.

07:01.288 --> 07:04.758
‐ Well, what about
the malpractice suit?

07:04.791 --> 07:05.759
‐ I dug into it.

07:05.792 --> 07:06.893
The payout
wouldn't have come close

07:06.927 --> 07:08.895
to covering your contract.

07:10.096 --> 07:11.431
‐ All right,
so what?

07:11.464 --> 07:14.467
You came over here
to tell me you got nothing?

07:14.501 --> 07:17.003
‐ This is why I asked
to meet you alone.

07:17.037 --> 07:20.006
[tense music]

07:20.040 --> 07:23.009
‐ My wife?
‐ Your second, right?

07:23.043 --> 07:24.844
♪ ♪

07:24.878 --> 07:26.846
‐ Does it matter?
‐ I don't know.

07:26.880 --> 07:27.981
But when I compared
her cell phone records

07:28.014 --> 07:28.949
against her calendar,

07:28.982 --> 07:31.184
some of the geo tags
didn't line up.

07:31.217 --> 07:33.386
Bottom line is,
she's hiding something.

07:33.420 --> 07:36.122
♪ ♪

07:36.156 --> 07:38.591
‐ I'm sure she can
clear all that up.

07:38.625 --> 07:41.027
‐ Great.
I hope so.

07:41.061 --> 07:42.529
But in my line of work,

07:42.562 --> 07:45.699
cases like these,
it's someone you know.

07:45.732 --> 07:47.901
Someone you're close to.

07:47.934 --> 07:49.569
The vast majority
of domestic Purges

07:49.602 --> 07:54.474
are committed by the spouse.

07:54.507 --> 07:59.579
‐ Open case B246 and scan
for facial features.

07:59.612 --> 08:02.482
[beeping]

08:02.515 --> 08:07.053
What do you think?
‐ Um, nada.

08:07.087 --> 08:08.955
He's hidden in every one.

08:08.989 --> 08:10.924
Plates‐‐they're from
out of state,

08:10.957 --> 08:12.926
so it will take some time
to run them.

08:12.959 --> 08:15.729
‐ He probably swaps them,
if he's this careful,

08:15.762 --> 08:18.131
but the system can search
for that numerical sequence

08:18.164 --> 08:21.468
from all cameras.
Type it in.

08:21.501 --> 08:24.904
[beeping]

08:24.938 --> 08:31.911
♪ ♪

08:31.945 --> 08:33.446
Hmm.
There it is.

08:33.480 --> 08:36.416
‐ What?
‐ Armored truck.

08:36.449 --> 08:38.251
Probably on a bank run.

08:38.284 --> 08:40.520
♪ ♪

08:40.553 --> 08:42.756
Remember the crew
that robbed First Parish?

08:42.789 --> 08:44.257
‐ Clearly not as well
as you do.

08:44.290 --> 08:46.626
‐ They took great care
to hide their faces,

08:46.659 --> 08:50.196
and this picture was taken
a few blocks from that bank.

08:50.230 --> 08:52.532
I'll pull up the logs
from that Purge Night.

08:52.565 --> 08:54.768
Let's see if it's an ID match.

08:54.801 --> 09:01.808
♪ ♪

09:01.841 --> 09:04.044
‐ Can't call it
a positive match.

09:04.077 --> 09:05.045
Can you?

09:05.078 --> 09:10.617
♪ ♪

09:10.650 --> 09:12.052
‐ Huh.

09:12.085 --> 09:15.722
♪ ♪

09:15.755 --> 09:18.958
No.

09:18.992 --> 09:21.861
Who the hell is this guy?

09:21.895 --> 09:24.798
[woman moaning]

09:24.831 --> 09:31.805
♪ ♪

09:38.244 --> 09:40.313
‐ You okay?
‐ What?

09:40.346 --> 09:44.818
‐ I said, "Are you all right?"
‐ Yeah, I'm good.

09:44.851 --> 09:48.855
‐ Um, we can stop.
‐ Do you want to?

09:48.888 --> 09:51.925
‐ Yeah, I don't know.
You're not even looking at me.

09:51.958 --> 09:53.593
‐ I'm sorry.

09:53.626 --> 09:56.596
[both breathing heavily]

09:56.629 --> 09:58.331
♪ ♪

09:58.364 --> 09:59.732
‐ [moans]

09:59.766 --> 10:03.670
♪ ♪

10:03.703 --> 10:07.173
[moaning]

10:07.207 --> 10:09.075
‐ [screams]

10:09.109 --> 10:10.176
God damn it.

10:10.210 --> 10:11.511
Fuck.

10:13.213 --> 10:14.981
Shit.

10:15.014 --> 10:22.055
♪ ♪

10:23.123 --> 10:26.359
[exhales sharply]

10:26.392 --> 10:29.829
‐ What's going on with you?

10:29.863 --> 10:31.564
‐ I don't know
what's going on.

10:31.598 --> 10:33.600
♪ ♪

10:33.633 --> 10:34.701
‐ Here.

10:40.607 --> 10:43.877
Try to relax.

10:43.910 --> 10:50.917
♪ ♪

10:55.622 --> 10:57.924
‐ I should see if Turner has
some blue pills or something.

10:57.957 --> 11:00.260
‐ You know those things
seriously mess up

11:00.293 --> 11:04.330
your sperm count, right?
‐ I was kidding.

11:04.364 --> 11:08.868
‐ What you should do
is punch Turner in the face.

11:08.902 --> 11:13.039
He left you alone,
and seriously,

11:13.072 --> 11:17.010
if you want to try something,

11:17.043 --> 11:19.746
strawberries are like
nature's blue pill.

11:19.779 --> 11:21.948
[chuckles]

11:21.981 --> 11:26.252
‐ How do you even know that?
‐ [chuckles]

11:26.286 --> 11:27.320
CNN.

11:33.660 --> 11:36.629
[tense music]

11:36.663 --> 11:43.670
♪ ♪

11:53.346 --> 11:53.613
[tense music]

11:57.116 --> 11:59.185
‐ Swapped plates.
Just like you thought.

12:01.854 --> 12:05.024
‐ Pull up the sector grid.

12:05.058 --> 12:09.896
People tend to follow patterns.
Play it.

12:09.929 --> 12:11.898
Go back a day.

12:11.931 --> 12:14.968
[beeps]

12:14.968 --> 12:18.071
Go back a week.
Same time.

12:18.104 --> 12:20.106
[beeps]

12:20.139 --> 12:23.076
‐ He's punctual.
‐ No one's that punctual.

12:23.109 --> 12:25.612
‐ You are.

12:25.645 --> 12:27.080
‐ As far as we can tell,

12:27.113 --> 12:29.249
this guy hasn't
broken the law.

12:29.282 --> 12:32.819
♪ ♪

12:32.852 --> 12:36.289
But you're not this good at
hiding unless you need to be.

12:36.322 --> 12:38.224
Follow him down that street.

12:38.258 --> 12:39.292
‐ There's no cameras
down that street.

12:39.325 --> 12:40.560
It's a dead zone.

12:40.593 --> 12:42.996
‐ Hmm.

12:43.029 --> 12:43.930
He's good.
I'll give him that.

12:43.963 --> 12:45.131
‐ Mm‐hmm.

12:45.164 --> 12:48.401
‐ He knows exactly where we're
looking and where we're not.

12:48.434 --> 12:50.336
I'll go check
on that dead zone.

12:50.370 --> 12:52.572
What are the timestamps
on the hits?

12:52.605 --> 12:57.310
‐ Uh, between 9:00 and 9:11.

12:57.343 --> 12:59.212
‐ Then we have our window.

12:59.245 --> 13:01.948
‐ [exhales sharply]

13:01.981 --> 13:07.453
♪ ♪

13:07.487 --> 13:10.857
‐ Michelle?
‐ Be out in a sec.

13:10.890 --> 13:14.961
♪ ♪

13:14.994 --> 13:17.463
[phone clicks]

13:17.497 --> 13:24.470
♪ ♪

13:24.504 --> 13:27.974
We got a notice about an HOA
meeting on Wednesday.

13:30.410 --> 13:33.012
Are you coming with me?

13:33.046 --> 13:36.182
‐ Uh, no thanks.
I hate those things.

13:36.215 --> 13:37.950
‐ You mean you don't
want to hear

13:37.984 --> 13:40.987
Oscar and April discuss
the merits of exposed brick?

13:41.020 --> 13:42.455
‐ Uh, you can take notes,
right?

13:43.156 --> 13:44.357
‐ [groans]

13:44.390 --> 13:46.659
And what did
the investigator say?

13:46.693 --> 13:48.995
Did she have any leads?

13:49.028 --> 13:49.996
‐ Nothing really.

13:50.029 --> 13:52.865
Just her telling me
who she thinks didn't do it.

13:52.899 --> 13:55.168
‐ Well, couldn't she have
just called then?

13:55.201 --> 13:57.003
‐ I don't know, Michelle.
This is all new to me.

13:57.036 --> 14:00.139
I mean what do you
want me to say?

14:00.173 --> 14:01.507
‐ I don't want you
to say anything.

14:01.541 --> 14:02.475
Not if you're gonna
say it like that.

14:02.508 --> 14:06.346
[dramatic music]

14:06.379 --> 14:07.914
‐ I'm sorry.

14:07.947 --> 14:11.184
I'm just‐‐I'm just tired.

14:11.217 --> 14:16.289
♪ ♪

14:16.322 --> 14:19.325
So where are you going?
You just got back.

14:19.359 --> 14:21.060
‐ I got a client
meeting downtown,

14:21.094 --> 14:23.930
and then I'm meeting up
with the girls for drinks.

14:23.963 --> 14:25.698
‐ Drinks?
Again?

14:25.732 --> 14:27.333
‐ [chuckles]

14:27.367 --> 14:29.635
You are no place
to lecture me.

14:29.669 --> 14:33.406
‐ All right.
Will you be back for dinner?

14:33.439 --> 14:35.942
‐ Not sure,
so don't wait on me.

14:35.975 --> 14:42.448
♪ ♪

14:42.482 --> 14:44.417
[door closes]

14:44.450 --> 14:51.491
♪ ♪

14:52.725 --> 14:55.695
[beeping]

14:55.728 --> 15:02.902
♪ ♪

15:04.170 --> 15:07.073
[motorcycle engine rumbling]

15:07.106 --> 15:10.076
[camera shutter clicking]

15:10.109 --> 15:17.083
♪ ♪

15:34.100 --> 15:34.934
‐ Shit.

15:36.636 --> 15:39.605
‐ So how will you
use this freedom?

15:39.639 --> 15:44.243
Will you right some wrongs?

15:44.277 --> 15:46.612
Will you heal?

15:46.646 --> 15:48.347
Will you hurt?

15:48.381 --> 15:49.449
Will you‐‐

15:49.482 --> 15:52.285
[cows mooing]

15:52.318 --> 15:54.654
[car door thuds]

15:54.687 --> 16:01.661
♪ ♪

16:01.694 --> 16:04.363
‐ You lost or something?

16:04.397 --> 16:05.431
‐ No.
I was‐‐

16:06.566 --> 16:08.601
Online, it‐‐it said

16:08.634 --> 16:13.139
this place is good for
getting out aggression.

16:13.172 --> 16:15.374
‐ Yeah, that's right.
You ever done this before?

16:15.408 --> 16:18.277
[cows mooing]

16:18.311 --> 16:20.546
♪ ♪

16:20.580 --> 16:22.648
Sign here.

16:22.682 --> 16:24.250
‐ What is this?
‐ It's a release.

16:24.283 --> 16:27.720
Waives all your rights,
in case of an accident.

16:27.753 --> 16:31.123
‐ What kind of accident?
‐ They're animals.

16:31.157 --> 16:33.693
They don't want to die.
Cash only.

16:33.726 --> 16:38.531
♪ ♪

16:38.564 --> 16:40.333
Let's get you dressed.

16:40.366 --> 16:43.336
♪ ♪

16:43.369 --> 16:45.805
Large should suit you
just fine.

16:45.838 --> 16:53.045
♪ ♪

16:56.215 --> 16:58.451
Now, make sure you secure
the neck and the sleeves,

16:58.484 --> 17:01.354
or blood'll find a way in.
Always does.

17:01.387 --> 17:08.394
♪ ♪

17:10.696 --> 17:12.532
Now you get to choose.

17:12.565 --> 17:19.572
♪ ♪

17:32.552 --> 17:34.287
Oh, and one more thing.

17:34.320 --> 17:35.721
Preserve the meat.

17:35.755 --> 17:40.593
♪ ♪

17:40.626 --> 17:43.596
[cows mooing]

17:43.629 --> 17:50.670
♪ ♪

18:04.317 --> 18:04.617
[dramatic music]

18:07.153 --> 18:14.193
♪ ♪

18:14.961 --> 18:16.963
‐ [chuckles]
There's no way.

18:16.996 --> 18:18.965
♪ ♪

18:18.998 --> 18:21.901
[phone beeps]

18:21.934 --> 18:26.172
♪ ♪

18:26.205 --> 18:28.341
Where the hell are you going?

18:28.374 --> 18:35.147
♪ ♪

18:35.181 --> 18:38.317
[gunshots and screams echoing
distantly]

18:38.351 --> 18:39.318
[garbled speech]

18:39.352 --> 18:41.654
‐ You go left.
I'll go right.

18:41.687 --> 18:48.894
♪ ♪

18:54.567 --> 18:56.335
‐ [shouting]

18:56.369 --> 18:59.305
‐ Hey, take it easy.
‐ [shouting]

18:59.338 --> 19:02.308
[all grunting]

19:02.341 --> 19:06.979
[blows landing]

19:07.013 --> 19:08.114
‐ Ryan, you good?

19:08.147 --> 19:11.384
[gunfire]

19:11.417 --> 19:14.520
‐ Snipers.

19:14.553 --> 19:15.888
They've only seen me.

19:15.921 --> 19:17.089
You guys should
get out of here.

19:17.123 --> 19:19.025
‐ We're not leaving you.
‐ This isn't up for debate.

19:19.058 --> 19:21.560
When I lay down fire you move.
Go.

19:21.594 --> 19:28.601
♪ ♪

19:31.604 --> 19:36.242
[both grunting]

19:36.275 --> 19:39.211
‐ Ryan, stop.

19:39.245 --> 19:42.982
‐ Reynolds, what the fuck
are you doing out here?

19:43.015 --> 19:45.951
‐ Easy does it, officer.

19:45.985 --> 19:48.354
Get him up.

19:48.387 --> 19:50.656
Come on.
Get him up.

19:50.690 --> 19:53.693
[crickets chirping
and guns clicking]

20:02.334 --> 20:04.503
‐ You've been working
with Caruso the whole time?

20:04.537 --> 20:08.441
♪ ♪

20:08.474 --> 20:11.577
How many cops you got out here?

20:11.610 --> 20:13.245
‐ All the smart ones.

20:13.279 --> 20:15.748
♪ ♪

20:15.781 --> 20:17.383
‐ Drop it.

20:17.416 --> 20:20.052
[gun cocking]

20:20.086 --> 20:23.289
♪ ♪

20:23.322 --> 20:24.724
[gun cocking]

20:24.757 --> 20:31.997
♪ ♪

20:33.065 --> 20:36.001
‐ Well, one person pulls
the trigger we're all dead.

20:36.035 --> 20:40.206
♪ ♪

20:40.239 --> 20:42.074
‐ Stand down.

20:42.108 --> 20:47.680
♪ ♪

20:47.713 --> 20:50.082
Get the fuck out of here, Ryan.

20:50.116 --> 20:57.123
♪ ♪

21:02.228 --> 21:04.263
I tried to tell you
to stay home tonight.

21:04.296 --> 21:06.165
You should have listened.

21:06.198 --> 21:10.236
♪ ♪

21:10.269 --> 21:13.239
[bell jingles]

21:13.272 --> 21:16.242
[rock music playing]

21:16.275 --> 21:23.215
♪ ♪

21:23.249 --> 21:26.652
‐ Got your message.
‐ What happened to Doug?

21:26.685 --> 21:28.587
‐ I haven't talked to him.

21:28.621 --> 21:32.625
[tense music]

21:32.658 --> 21:35.427
Why'd you call the meeting?

21:35.461 --> 21:38.531
[pigs squealing]

21:38.564 --> 21:41.200
♪ ♪

21:41.233 --> 21:44.203
[cows mooing]

21:44.236 --> 21:51.277
♪ ♪

21:56.282 --> 21:58.150
‐ It's okay, kid.

21:58.184 --> 21:59.552
Not everybody has
the stomach for it.

21:59.585 --> 22:06.625
♪ ♪

23:14.560 --> 23:16.595
♪ ♪

23:16.629 --> 23:19.598
[stairs creaking]

23:19.632 --> 23:21.600
♪ ♪

23:21.634 --> 23:25.537
[distant sniffling]

23:25.571 --> 23:32.611
♪ ♪

23:32.645 --> 23:33.545
‐ It's okay.

23:33.579 --> 23:35.547
We all know what
you're feeling.

23:35.581 --> 23:37.616
This is a safe space.

23:37.650 --> 23:40.719
‐ [crying]

23:40.753 --> 23:44.456
I try to pretend
everything is okay.

23:44.490 --> 23:46.325
‐ You don't have to pretend.

23:46.358 --> 23:49.795
♪ ♪

23:49.828 --> 23:53.465
‐ I still can't sleep
with the lights off.

23:53.499 --> 23:55.768
‐ And what about your husband?

23:55.801 --> 23:57.569
Is there any chance
he could come here with you?

23:57.603 --> 24:00.372
Share his story?

24:00.406 --> 24:02.274
‐ He's so paranoid.

24:02.308 --> 24:03.776
I know he wouldn't want me

24:03.809 --> 24:04.977
talking about what happened

24:05.010 --> 24:07.479
to a bunch of
anonymous strangers.

24:07.513 --> 24:09.848
And he's so focused on

24:09.882 --> 24:16.755
figuring out who
came after him that sometimes‐‐

24:16.789 --> 24:18.691
‐ Whenever you're ready.
‐ It's okay.

24:18.724 --> 24:21.327
‐ [exhales sharply]

24:21.360 --> 24:25.297
Sometimes he forgets
who's right by his side.

24:25.331 --> 24:28.400
♪ ♪

24:28.434 --> 24:32.338
[sniffs]

24:32.371 --> 24:35.341
‐ I think we all
know how you feel.

24:35.374 --> 24:38.811
Let's just go around the room
and share our Purge traumas.

24:38.844 --> 24:40.846
[bell jingles]

24:40.879 --> 24:43.849
[rock music playing]

24:43.882 --> 24:50.322
♪ ♪

24:50.356 --> 24:52.458
‐ I found out why there wasn't
a bigger haul.

24:52.491 --> 24:56.495
♪ ♪

24:56.528 --> 25:01.000
The money was never supposed
to be in that bag.

25:01.033 --> 25:03.268
‐ What?

25:03.302 --> 25:05.337
‐ Federal law only requires

25:05.371 --> 25:07.906
that they keep
a certain amount on hand.

25:07.940 --> 25:11.710
Trucks move the rest to
a private airstrip in Overton.

25:11.744 --> 25:13.846
The banks put the money
in the air,

25:13.879 --> 25:15.547
and they keep the planes
up there all night,

25:15.581 --> 25:18.350
so it can't be touched.

25:18.384 --> 25:21.420
I told you I'd find
something out, and I did.

25:21.453 --> 25:24.556
They're moving that money,

25:24.590 --> 25:27.826
and we can take it before it
ever leaves the ground.

25:27.860 --> 25:31.497
[tense music]

25:31.530 --> 25:33.632
Anybody listening
to what I just said?

25:33.665 --> 25:36.568
‐ We're always listening.

25:36.602 --> 25:39.438
It's just not working out
so well these days.

25:39.471 --> 25:41.340
♪ ♪

25:41.373 --> 25:45.244
‐ This is the score to fund
the rest of our lives.

25:45.277 --> 25:47.579
This is like breaking
into the bank's bank.

25:47.613 --> 25:49.014
‐ It just sounds
dangerous, man.

25:49.048 --> 25:54.053
I got kids to think about.
‐ I'm thinking about your kids.

25:54.086 --> 25:57.790
We are busting our asses
every year to stay afloat.

25:57.823 --> 26:00.459
My mother, your family,
your mortgage.

26:00.492 --> 26:03.629
Working for hourly
is not gonna cut it for us.

26:03.662 --> 26:08.867
♪ ♪

26:08.901 --> 26:10.536
‐ Okay, sure.

26:10.569 --> 26:12.071
What happened on
the force limited our options.

26:12.104 --> 26:13.205
‐ Limited options?

26:13.238 --> 26:14.473
What, no pension?
No college education?

26:14.506 --> 26:16.875
Just a bunch of scars,
a busted‐up liver,

26:16.909 --> 26:19.445
and the joys
of living with PTSD.

26:19.478 --> 26:21.780
♪ ♪

26:21.814 --> 26:23.382
‐ I don't know, Ryan.

26:23.415 --> 26:26.919
‐ Hey, we do this.
We do it our way.

26:26.952 --> 26:31.890
We play by the rules, and we
always have each other's backs.

26:31.924 --> 26:35.427
I'm not gonna do this
without you.

26:35.461 --> 26:41.100
We pull this off
we're gonna be very happy.

26:41.133 --> 26:45.637
[cell phone vibrating]

26:45.671 --> 26:49.608
♪ ♪

26:49.641 --> 26:50.609
‐ Hey, it's Darren.
I got the message.

26:50.642 --> 26:51.944
You wanted to talk to me
about Dr. Adams?

26:51.977 --> 26:54.480
‐ Yes.
Great.

26:54.513 --> 26:56.415
Meet me at the cafe on Jackson.

27:04.723 --> 27:04.990
[tense music]

27:06.024 --> 27:08.861
‐ I need a word.
‐ Rough night?

27:08.894 --> 27:11.697
‐ You let my team walk
right into a death trap.

27:11.730 --> 27:13.532
‐ Everything I did was legal.

27:13.565 --> 27:15.901
‐ How much is Caruso
paying you for protection?

27:15.934 --> 27:18.437
‐ Enough to put my kid
through college.

27:18.470 --> 27:21.440
‐ Would you fucking listen
to yourself?

27:21.473 --> 27:23.008
How many other kids
are gonna die,

27:23.041 --> 27:25.878
because of the drugs
you're letting into the city?

27:25.911 --> 27:29.615
This doesn't have
the same weight it used to.

27:29.648 --> 27:32.017
‐ It's a new world out there.
I chose to adapt.

27:32.050 --> 27:33.886
‐ Yeah?
Well, so am I.

27:33.919 --> 27:35.954
‐ Well, good luck out there.
You're gonna need it.

27:35.988 --> 27:38.357
‐ What does that mean?

27:38.390 --> 27:40.893
‐ It means you walk away
from us you pay a price.

27:40.926 --> 27:42.895
You try and get a city job,
I'll stop it.

27:42.928 --> 27:43.629
Private security?

27:43.662 --> 27:44.963
I'll hear about it.

27:44.997 --> 27:46.298
You'll be working as a bouncer

27:46.331 --> 27:48.867
in a shitty strip club
in a week.

27:48.901 --> 27:52.571
All you know
is violence and vice.

27:52.604 --> 27:54.540
You're fucked, Ryan.

27:54.573 --> 27:56.842
You just don't see it yet.

27:56.875 --> 28:01.647
♪ ♪

28:01.680 --> 28:03.916
‐ Ryan?

28:03.949 --> 28:05.317
‐ You guys don't have
to do this.

28:05.350 --> 28:08.754
♪ ♪

28:08.787 --> 28:10.355
‐ Yeah, we do.

28:10.389 --> 28:17.396
♪ ♪

28:19.698 --> 28:22.634
[rock music playing]

28:22.668 --> 28:28.774
♪ ♪

28:28.807 --> 28:31.743
[tense music]

28:31.777 --> 28:35.781
♪ ♪

28:35.814 --> 28:38.850
‐ Everybody has
the urge to Purge.

28:38.884 --> 28:40.619
Not everyone has the courage

28:40.652 --> 28:42.354
to listen to
their inner voice,

28:42.387 --> 28:45.624
the voice that begs
them to rise up.

28:45.657 --> 28:48.560
And can you stand
another year of life

28:48.594 --> 28:51.463
with this poison
inside of you?

28:51.496 --> 28:55.133
You'll do a lot of good work
on Purge Night.

28:55.167 --> 28:58.403
But you won't be able
to get it all done.

28:58.437 --> 28:59.538
People will always
surprise you

28:59.571 --> 29:02.741
when they don't want to die.

29:02.774 --> 29:04.643
But when you
embrace the Purge,

29:04.676 --> 29:09.948
when you commit to the healing
power of its violence,

29:09.982 --> 29:13.452
anything can happen.

29:13.485 --> 29:14.720
What will you‐‐

29:23.428 --> 29:24.229
‐ Evening.

29:24.263 --> 29:27.566
[car door slams]

29:27.599 --> 29:29.067
What can I do for you?

29:29.101 --> 29:31.403
‐ How are the strawberries?
‐ Oh, they're delicious.

29:31.436 --> 29:34.873
Well here.
Just try one, on the house.

29:38.443 --> 29:39.945
What's the verdict?

29:40.812 --> 29:42.347
‐ Delicious.
‐ [laughs]

29:42.381 --> 29:44.583
That's what I like to hear.

29:44.616 --> 29:45.751
‐ I'll take one.
‐ All righty.

29:45.784 --> 29:47.052
That's $5.

29:51.390 --> 29:53.625
Here you go.

29:53.659 --> 29:55.827
‐ You, uh, get many
customers out here?

29:55.861 --> 29:57.663
‐ Oh, it picks up on
the weekends, you know.

29:57.696 --> 30:01.033
‐ I'm sorry.
I gave you a 20.

30:01.066 --> 30:03.769
‐ Uh, you gave me a 10.

30:03.802 --> 30:07.005
‐ No, I only have 20s
in my wallet.

30:07.039 --> 30:09.408
So I think you owe me money.

30:09.441 --> 30:12.644
‐ Oh, no, son.
That's not right.

30:12.678 --> 30:15.714
‐ Well, I'm not lying to you.

30:15.747 --> 30:20.018
I know what I gave you.
Can you‐‐can you just look?

30:20.052 --> 30:21.553
‐ All right.

30:21.586 --> 30:23.822
Yeah, right‐‐right there.
See? 10.

30:23.855 --> 30:25.791
[tense music]

30:25.824 --> 30:29.194
‐ That's not mine.
‐ Well, you gave me a 10, son.

30:29.227 --> 30:31.163
I'm sorry.

30:31.196 --> 30:35.067
‐ Dude, just give me my change.
‐ I did give you your change.

30:35.100 --> 30:38.070
You're holding it.

30:38.103 --> 30:40.138
Hey, hey, hey!
Give me my money.

30:40.172 --> 30:42.074
Oh, God.
What are you doing?

30:42.107 --> 30:43.508
You cut me.

30:43.542 --> 30:46.511
[knife slicing]
[both grunting]

30:46.545 --> 30:48.046
♪ ♪

30:48.080 --> 30:51.917
[both shouting]

30:51.950 --> 30:53.919
Help me!
Help!

30:53.952 --> 30:55.587
[both grunting]

30:55.620 --> 30:58.590
[screaming]

30:58.623 --> 31:01.560
♪ ♪

31:01.593 --> 31:03.929
[screaming]
God!

31:03.962 --> 31:06.932
[knife stabbing]
[screaming]

31:06.965 --> 31:14.005
♪ ♪

31:16.742 --> 31:19.711
[rock smacking against head]

31:19.745 --> 31:26.752
♪ ♪

31:38.196 --> 31:38.497
[dramatic music]

31:39.531 --> 31:42.467
♪ ♪

31:42.501 --> 31:44.603
[bell jingles]

31:44.636 --> 31:47.072
♪ ♪

31:47.105 --> 31:51.143
‐ Mr. Moore.
Hi, I'm Esme.

31:51.176 --> 31:53.111
Thank you for meeting me.

31:53.145 --> 31:56.415
I just need five minutes.
That's all.

31:56.448 --> 31:58.483
‐ Okay.

31:58.517 --> 32:02.921
All right, uh,
what do you want to show me?

32:02.954 --> 32:04.456
‐ These.

32:04.489 --> 32:06.892
They belonged
to Professor Adams.

32:09.628 --> 32:13.498
‐ You're kidding me.
‐ What is it?

32:13.532 --> 32:15.467
‐ [chuckles]

32:15.500 --> 32:16.735
I didn't even know she had
any active trials.

32:16.768 --> 32:18.470
Wow.

32:18.503 --> 32:20.238
‐ Do you know anyone else
who might have been involved

32:20.272 --> 32:21.239
with the research?

32:25.677 --> 32:27.212
‐ I'm sorry.

32:27.245 --> 32:28.814
Um, how'd you come
across these again?

32:28.847 --> 32:30.849
‐ I found them.
‐ Yeah, where'd you find them?

32:30.882 --> 32:32.818
‐ At her home.

32:32.851 --> 32:35.387
‐ Okay, and how'd
that come about?

32:35.420 --> 32:36.388
‐ Uh, yeah.
I'm sorry.

32:36.421 --> 32:37.789
Uh, of course.

32:37.823 --> 32:40.325
I‐‐I work for
NFFA surveillance.

32:40.358 --> 32:41.893
‐ Yeah, you need
to leave me alone right now.

32:41.927 --> 32:43.161
‐ No, I'm not investigating
Dr. Adams.

32:43.195 --> 32:45.964
I'm trying to find out
why she was killed.

32:45.997 --> 32:50.335
Please, just‐‐just hear me out.

32:50.368 --> 32:51.803
Please.

32:56.274 --> 32:58.443
I owe her my life.

32:58.477 --> 33:01.279
She helped me and my sister
through a dark time.

33:01.313 --> 33:06.751
I watched her die,
on Purge Night.

33:06.785 --> 33:10.689
Now, you spoke about wanting
to know why she was Purged.

33:13.191 --> 33:18.196
Whatever she was researching,
it was important to her,

33:18.230 --> 33:22.567
and she was protecting
these when she died.

33:22.601 --> 33:25.504
So I'm just asking you
to help me.

33:25.537 --> 33:27.339
Please.

33:27.372 --> 33:32.244
♪ ♪

33:32.277 --> 33:36.548
‐ I'll take a look at 'em.

33:36.581 --> 33:38.617
‐ Thank you.

33:38.650 --> 33:45.724
♪ ♪

33:48.793 --> 33:52.197
‐ Hi.
‐ Hi.

33:52.230 --> 33:54.032
♪ ♪

33:54.065 --> 33:55.901
You cooked?

33:55.934 --> 33:57.702
‐ Shocking.
I know.

33:59.538 --> 34:04.242
‐ But I thought I told you
to eat without me.

34:04.276 --> 34:08.747
‐ I know, but I wanted to wait.

34:08.780 --> 34:10.549
How was the client meeting?

34:10.582 --> 34:13.718
‐ Hmm?
Oh, it was, uh, good.

34:13.752 --> 34:15.820
He, uh, wants to hire me.

34:15.854 --> 34:16.988
‐ Okay.

34:17.022 --> 34:18.657
I'll get you a drink
to celebrate.

34:18.690 --> 34:21.993
Hold on.
I hope you're hungry.

34:22.027 --> 34:26.765
‐ Starving.
Thanks for cooking.

34:29.401 --> 34:34.039
‐ Come here.
Sit.

34:39.377 --> 34:40.645
‐ Oh, thank you.

34:43.481 --> 34:44.883
How was your day?

34:45.784 --> 34:50.922
‐ Well, better,
now that you're home.

34:55.860 --> 34:57.596
‐ Mmm.

35:02.801 --> 35:08.840
‐ Um, I'm sorry about earlier.

35:08.873 --> 35:10.475
‐ Me too.

35:10.508 --> 35:12.711
♪ ♪

35:12.744 --> 35:14.646
[tense music]

35:14.679 --> 35:17.248
‐ Hey, Esme.
Well?

35:17.282 --> 35:19.050
‐ Huh?
‐ Mystery man?

35:19.084 --> 35:20.885
‐ Yeah.
Working on it.

35:20.919 --> 35:24.623
♪ ♪

35:24.656 --> 35:26.124
[computer beeps]

35:26.157 --> 35:27.792
♪ ♪

35:27.826 --> 35:30.895
[beeping]

35:30.929 --> 35:38.003
♪ ♪

36:06.431 --> 36:06.698
[tense music]

36:09.134 --> 36:16.241
♪ ♪

36:29.487 --> 36:31.823
[door squeaks]

36:58.683 --> 37:01.820
‐ [moans]

37:01.853 --> 37:03.354
Ben?

37:07.859 --> 37:09.728
Hey.

37:09.761 --> 37:16.735
♪ ♪

37:23.374 --> 37:26.377
‐ I haven't been acting
like myself.

37:26.411 --> 37:27.879
‐ Yeah.

37:27.912 --> 37:32.383
♪ ♪

37:32.417 --> 37:35.019
Ben, what happened?

37:35.053 --> 37:36.888
‐ I Purged.

37:36.921 --> 37:41.025
♪ ♪

37:41.059 --> 37:43.995
I stabbed him over and over.

37:44.028 --> 37:45.630
‐ Hey.

37:45.663 --> 37:50.001
♪ ♪

37:50.034 --> 37:52.537
I just have one question.

37:52.570 --> 37:55.940
Was it something you had to do?

37:55.974 --> 37:58.510
♪ ♪

37:58.543 --> 37:59.844
‐ Yes.

37:59.878 --> 38:03.548
♪ ♪

38:03.581 --> 38:07.352
‐ Then you're a good person,

38:07.385 --> 38:09.487
and I love you.

38:09.521 --> 38:14.559
♪ ♪

38:14.592 --> 38:19.731
What happens on Purge Night
stays on Purge Night, okay?

38:19.764 --> 38:23.535
♪ ♪

38:23.568 --> 38:24.803
‐ Yeah.

38:24.836 --> 38:26.938
Yeah, Purge Night.

38:26.971 --> 38:30.742
♪ ♪

38:30.775 --> 38:32.877
[groans]

38:32.911 --> 38:39.918
♪ ♪

38:53.631 --> 38:59.404
‐ Did you have strawberries?
‐ Hmm.

38:59.437 --> 39:02.073
‐ [laughs]

39:02.106 --> 39:09.314
♪ ♪

39:14.552 --> 39:16.621
‐ Is this seat taken?
No?

39:16.654 --> 39:18.056
Good.

39:18.089 --> 39:20.925
I'm not catching you
at a bad time, am I?

39:20.959 --> 39:23.928
‐ Um, do I know you?
‐ Well, I don't know.

39:23.962 --> 39:26.798
You certainly seem to.

39:26.831 --> 39:30.401
Why were you
following me yesterday?

39:30.435 --> 39:32.470
